    "section_xb8kUP": {
      "type": "section",
      "blocks": {
        "text_NphQz8": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Sustainability In Every Step</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h2",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_GwGca3": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>These are some of the ways in which we make sustainability the baseline of our work. To protect the soil, reduce harm, and begin healing our relationship with the way we take from the land.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "none",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "accordion_WmxRHH": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "name": "t:names.accordion",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "caret",
            "dividers": true,
            "single_open": true,
            "type_preset": "h5",
            "inherit_color_scheme": true,
            "color_scheme": "",
            "border": "none",
            "border_width": 1,
            "border_opacity": 100,
            "border_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {
            "accordion_row_Ux9WVG": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "Responsible Sourcing Beyond the Estate",
                "open_by_default": true,
                "icon": "none",
                "image_upload": "shopify://shop_images/Vector_29.png",
                "width": 28
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_KBtRFG": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>Not every botanical or material we work with can be grown at Cala Falcó. When we source beyond the estate, we do so with great care, prioritising suppliers who work with transparency, ethical practices, and a genuine respect for the land.</p><p>We look for partners whose values align with our own. Thoughtful cultivation, responsible harvesting, traceability and a commitment to quality that begins at origin. Sourcing is never only about obtaining an ingredient, it is about extending the integrity of our system beyond the boundaries of the estate.</p>",
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_KBtRFG"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_dFcyn9": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "Low Impact Production",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "image_upload": "shopify://shop_images/5e5215b8-ebc4-41e2-9090-50e92970e028-removebg-preview.png",
                "width": 32
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_ELdDBT": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>The way something is made matters as much as what it is made from.</p><p>Our production approach is guided by care, restraint and intentionality. We favour small-batch processes over industrial scale, allowing for greater precision, lower waste, and a closer relationship with the materials we work with.</p><p>Where possible, we seek lower impact energy systems and more efficient production methods, always looking for ways to reduce waste and improve how resources are used over time.</p>",
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_ELdDBT"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_EreKQW": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "Packaging & Materials",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "image_upload": "shopify://shop_images/Vector_31.png",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_wgwLJD": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>We believe packaging should protect the product without creating unnecessary burden on the planet.</p><p>For this reason, we prioritise materials that can be recycled, reused, composted, or biodegraded whenever possible. We work to reduce plastics, avoid excess and design packaging that is as minimal and purposeful as it can be. Refillable formats, reusable vessels, and reduced outer packaging all form part of this thinking.</p><p>For us, good design is not only about beauty, it is also about responsibility. Choosing materials and formats that minimise waste while preserving the integrity of the object.</p>",
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_wgwLJD"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_7gHXEB": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "Waste & Circular Thinking",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "image_upload": "shopify://shop_images/af0fa225-1a07-4161-9ff4-b1daf7fb01b4-removebg-preview.png",
                "width": 28
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_qttLgV": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>We try to think in cycles rather than in straight lines.</p><p>Across the estate and in production, we look for ways to ensure that what might otherwise be considered waste can return to the system with new value. Plant matter can be composted and returned to the soil. Biomass from pruning can be used to protect and nourish the land. By-products from distillation or extraction can sometimes be reformulated, repurposed, or transformed into new raw materials and products.</p><p>This circular way of thinking allows us to reduce waste, extend the life of materials, and build systems in which one process can nourish another.</p>",
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_qttLgV"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_aXUQk3": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "Energy Use & Carbon",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "image_upload": "shopify://shop_images/Vector_30.png",
                "width": 26
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_E74x3L": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>We believe carbon responsibility begins with practical choices.</p><p>Where possible, we seek to reduce emissions through local production, thoughtful sourcing, efficient logistics and lower-impact energy systems. We are interested not only in offsetting impact, but in reducing it at source through the way we design our operations.</p><p>Energy and carbon are part of a wider responsibility in building a system that is lighter, more efficient and more regenerative over time.</p>",
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_E74x3L"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_iCR8Dg": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "Small Batch",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "image_upload": "shopify://shop_images/Vector_28.png",
                "width": 24
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_qU9aLg": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>We do not believe sustainability is compatible with overproduction.</p><p>That is why we work in small batches, prioritising quality over quantity and long-term land health over short-term yield. This allows us to respond more carefully to the rhythms of the estate, the availability of raw materials and the integrity of each formulation.</p><p>Small-batch production also helps us avoid unnecessary excess, reduce waste, and remain close to every step of the process. It is a slower model, but a more responsible one.</p>",
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_qU9aLg"
              ]
            },
            "accordion_row_rP79zp": {
              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "Supporting Local Community",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "image_upload": "shopify://shop_images/af0fa225-1a07-4161-9ff4-b1daf7fb01b4-2-removebg-preview.png",
                "width": 26
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_jnGyB6": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>Sustainability also concerns the health of local relationships, knowledge and communities.</p><p>We value working with local growers, makers, and partners whose practices strengthen the cultural and ecological fabric of the island. We are also committed to collaborations that create social value, including work connected to agriculture, land care, and craft that can support inclusion and meaningful participation. Initiatives such as those developed with organisations like Fundació Estel de Llevant demostrate that regeneration can also be social, offering pathways for connection, and reintegration through work with the land. </p><p>In this sense, sustainability is not only about reducing harm. It is about creating systems that support life more fully, ecologically, materially and humanly.</p>",
                    "width": "100%",
                    "max_width": "none",
                    "alignment": "left",
                    "type_preset": "rte",
                    "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                    "font_size": "1rem",
                    "line_height": "normal",
                    "letter_spacing": "normal",
                    "case": "none",
                    "wrap": "pretty",
                    "color": "var(--color-foreground)",
                    "background": false,
                    "background_color": "#00000026",
                    "corner_radius": 0,
                    "padding-block-start": 0,
                    "padding-block-end": 0,
                    "padding-inline-start": 0,
                    "padding-inline-end": 0
                  },
                  "blocks": {}
                }
              },
              "block_order": [
                "text_jnGyB6"
              ]
            }
          },
          "block_order": [
            "accordion_row_Ux9WVG",
            "accordion_row_dFcyn9",
            "accordion_row_EreKQW",
            "accordion_row_7gHXEB",
            "accordion_row_aXUQk3",
            "accordion_row_iCR8Dg",
            "accordion_row_rP79zp"
          ]
        }
